history.text: What did you think of Sandra Bullock in this film?
I think she played an important roll as the mother. She was the one who really wanted to take "Big Mike" in and really showed compassion towards him despite his upbringing.
I agree! It really shows how even people that don't have a lot can still be successful.

That's true! You should never judge someone by their appearance because you never know what they are going through or if they need help. Sandra's character was also very strong. Taking in someone who you barely know would be difficult to do. I know that "Big Mike" was also scared to let others in. How do you think trust was built between the two characters?
